  "returns": "mindspore.nn.ReLU6classmindspore.nn.ReLU6[source]Compute ReLU6 activation function element-wise.ReLU6 is similar to ReLU with a upper limit of 6, which if the inputs are greater than 6, the outputs\nwill be suppressed to 6.\nIt computes element-wise as\\[Y = \\min(\\max(0, x), 6)\\]ReLU6 Activation Function Graph:Inputs:x(Tensor) - The input of ReLU6 with data type of float16 or float32 and that\nis a Tensor of any valid shape.Outputs:Tensor, which has the same type asx.RaisesTypeError– If dtype ofxis neither float16 nor float32.Supported Platforms:AscendGPUCPUExamples>>>importmindspore>>>frommindsporeimportTensor,nn>>>importnumpyasnp>>>x=Tensor(np.array([-1,-2,0,2,1]),mindspore.float16)>>>relu6=nn.ReLU6()>>>output=relu6(x)>>>print(output)[0. 0. 0. 2. 1.]",
